    <h1>PageRank</h1>
    <p class="description">Google's foundational link-authority algorithm — developed at Stanford in 1998 — that scores each page's importance based on the quality and quantity of incoming links. Public scores retired in 2016, but <strong>the algorithm still runs</strong> inside Google's ranking system.</p>
    <div class="post-meta">
